    "created_at": "2014-10-15T17:12:04Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-10-15T17:12:04Z",
    "body": "I don't think there's much risk of encouraging people to use `*const i8`s instead of `str`s and `String`s. They don't play nicely with the rest of the libraries and can only be used inside of `unsafe` blocks. The reason to do it would purely be to make writing FFI code a bit neater and less error-prone. And it's not like the c-prefix is being used for anything else.\n",
